]]\n[[Category:Norway youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Norway under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Norway international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:V\u00e5lerenga Fotball players]]\n[[Category:Manchester United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach players]]\n[[Category:Hull City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blackburn Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:A.F.C. Bournemouth players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Norwegian people of Gambian descent]]\n", "name_user": "Robby.is.on", "label": "safe", "comment": "Date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joshua_King_(footballer)"}
{"title_page": "Power Rangers Megaforce", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Power Rangers Megaforce\n| show_name_2              = Power Rangers Super Megaforce<br>Saban's Power Rangers Megaforce<br>Saban's Power Rangers Super Megaforce\n| image                    = Power Rangers Megaforce logo.png\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = The logo for ''Power Rangers Megaforce'' (first season)\n| genre                    = [[Action fiction|Action]]<br>[[Adventure fiction|Adventure]]<br>[[Science fiction]]<br>[[Superhero fiction|Superhero]]\n| creator                  = [[Haim Saban]] <br/> [[Toei Company]] <br/> [[Ishimori Productions]]\n| based_on                 = ''[[Tensou Sentai Goseiger]]'' & <br>''[[Kaizoku Sentai Gokaiger]]''<br>by [[Toei Company]]\n| developer                = [[Saban Brands]]<br>[[Toei Company]]\n| composer                 = [[Noam Kaniel]]\n| opentheme                = \"[[Go Go Power Rangers]]\"\n| director                 = [[Jonathan Tzachor]] <br/> Jonathan Brough <br/> James Barr <br/> Yuji Noguchi <br/> [[Isaac Florentine]] <br/> [[John Laing (director)|John Laing]] <br/> Charlie Haskell\n| list_episodes            = \n| starring                 = [[#Cast|See below]]\n| country                  = United States<br>Japan\n| location                 = [[Auckland, New Zealand]]<br>[[Kyoto, Japan]], & [[Tokyo, Japan]]\n| executive_producer       = [[Jonathan Tzachor]]<br/>[[Haim Saban]] (Super Megaforce)\n| producer                 = Sally Campbell <br/> Brian Casentini (Super Megaforce)\n| runtime                  = 23 minutes\n| company                  = [[Saban Capital Group|SCG Power Rangers]]<br> Power Rangers Productions, Ltd.<br>[[Toei Company, Ltd.]]\n| distributor              = [[Saban Capital Group|Saban Brands]]<br>[[Marvista Entertainment]] (International)\n| network                  = [[Nickelodeon]]\n| channel                  = \n| picture_format           = [[720p]]/[[1080p]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n| first_aired              = {{start date|2013|02|02}}\n| last_aired               = {{start date|2014|11|22}}\n| language                 = \n| num_seasons              = 2\n| num_episodes             = 42<ref name=MarVista/><ref name=MarVista2/> ([[List of Power Rangers Megaforce episodes|List of ''Megaforce'' episodes]], [[List of Power Rangers Super Megaforce episodes|List of ''Super Megaforce'' episodes]])\n| preceded_by              = ''[[Power Rangers Samurai|Power Rangers Super Samurai]]''\n| followed_by              = ''[[Power Rangers Dino Charge]]''\n}}\n\n'''''Power Rangers Megaforce''''' is the twentieth season of the long-running [[United States|American]] [[children's television program]] ''[[Power Rangers]]''. The show is produced by [[Saban Capital Group|SCG Power Rangers]] and began airing on [[Nickelodeon]] on February 2, 2013.<ref name=\"TV Guide\">{{cite news | url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Power-Rangers-Megaforce-Premiere-1059159.aspx?rss=news&partnerid=spi&profileid=05 | title=Exclusive: Find Out When Power Rangers Megaforce Premieres and Get a First Look at the Cast | work=TV Guide | date=January 16, 2013 | accessdate=January 16, 2013 | author=Ross, Robyn}}</ref> The show was part of the ''Power Rangers'' 20th anniversary.<ref name=MarVista>{{cite news|last=Dickson|first=Jeremy|title=MarVista unveils new Power Rangers Megaforce series|url=http://kidscreen.com/2012/08/29/marvista-unveils-new-power-rangers-megaforce-series/|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=KidScreen|date=August 30, 2012}}</ref><ref name=MarVista2>{{cite news|last=Whittock|first=Jesse|title=MarVista powers up for Mip|url=http://www.c21media.net/archives/87172|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=C21Media|date=August 29, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Saban Celebrates Power Rangers, Paul Frank|url=http://digital.licensemag.com/nxtbooks/advanstar/license_daily_20120612/index.php?startid=12|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=License Show Daily|date=June 12, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Saban Creates Power Rangers Avatars|url=http://www.licensemag.com/licensemag/Entertainment/Saban-Creates-Power-Rangers-Avatars/ArticleStandard/Article/detail/782010|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=LicenseMag|date=July 19, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Cynopsis: Kids! 06/12/12|url=http://www.cynopsis.com/editions/kids/061212/|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=Cynopsis|date=June 12, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120616132851/http://www.cynopsis.com/editions/kids/061212/|archivedate=June 16, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Whittock|first=Jesse|title=Power Rangers unveil Megaforce, C5 deal|url=http://www.c21media.net/archives/83060|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=C21Media|date=June 12, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Saban Brands inks deals with Mattel, Pan Am|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/losangeles/news/2012/06/13/saban-brands-inks-deals-with-mattel.html|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=Los Angeles Business Journal|date=June 13, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Comic-Con Takes Over San Diego|url=http://www.licensemag.com/licensemag/News/Comic-Con-Takes-Over-San-Diego/ArticleStandard/Article/detail/781099|accessdate=September 8, 2012|newspaper=LicenseMag|date=Jul 12, 2012}}</ref> ''Kidscreen'' reported that ''Megaforce'' will feature \"the return of many historic Rangers.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kidscreen.com/content/pdf/51545.pdf |title=Kidscreen May/June 2012 (page 54) |publisher=kidscreen.com}}</ref> ''Megaforce'' uses footage, costumes and props from the Japanese [[Super Sentai]] Series ''[[Tensou Sentai Goseiger]]''.\n\nThe second season, and twenty-first overall, is called '''''Power Rangers Super Megaforce'''''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sabanbrands.com/brands/power-rangers/ |title=Power Rangers &#124; Saban Brands Saban Brands |publisher=Sabanbrands.com |date=2013-06-14 |accessdate=2013-06-18}}</ref> and premiered on February 15, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvlistings.zap2it.com/tv/power-rangers-super-megaforce-super-megaforce/EP018720840001?aid=zap2it|title=Power Rangers Super Megaforce : Super Megaforce|publisher=Zap2It|accessdate=2014-02-07}}</ref> ''Super Megaforce'' uses footage, costumes and props from ''[[Kaizoku Sentai Gokaiger]]''.\n\n==Promotion==\nThe Megaforce Power Rangers appeared at the 2012 [[Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade]], along with the past Red Rangers from ''[[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]]'' through ''[[Power Rangers Super Samurai]]''. The Rangers' Super Megaforce forms later appeared alongside the Mighty Morphin' Rangers during the 2013 [[Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade]].\n\n==Plot==\n\n===Season 1: ''Megaforce''===\n{{main|List of Power Rangers Megaforce episodes}}\n[[File:Power Rangers Megaforce Cast at Power Morphicon 3. Photo taken by RangerCrew.jpg|thumb|right|The ''Megaforce'' cast at the ''[[Power Rangers]]'' [[fan convention]] Power Morphicon in 2012.]]\nWhen the evil [[List of Power Rangers Megaforce characters#Warstar Empire|Warstar]] aliens attack Earth, the supernatural guardian Gosei, assigned to protect the Earth by Zordon, and his faithful robot assistant Tensou recruit five teenagers with attitude to combat the invading forces. Equipped with powers that grant them mastery over martial arts and other forms of combat, the teenagers transform into the latest champions of good: The Power Rangers Megaforce.<ref>{{cite news|title=Saban Brands' Power Rangers Megaforce to Premiere on Nickelodeon in Early 2013|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/saban-brands-power-rangers-megaforce-to-premiere-on-nickelodeon-in-early-2013-158462995.html|accessdate=December 30, 2012|newspaper=PR Newswire|date=June 11, 2012}}</ref>\nit's the best\n\n===Season 2: ''Super Megaforce''===\n{{main|List of Power Rangers Super Megaforce episodes}}\nIn the second ''Super Megaforce'' season, when an alien armada led by Prince Vekar - the brother of Vrak - plans to invade the Earth, Gosei gives the Megaforce Rangers new Morphers and special keys to allow them to become the Super Megaforce Rangers and also imbues them with the power to transform into any past \"Legendary\" Power Rangers. In course of time, due to their virtues and fighting spirit, they unlock various megazords of the past rangers (meeting several along the way.). An alien named Orion, whose home world was destroyed by the armada, then joins their ranks as the Silver Ranger, and gets all the legendary Sixth Ranger along with those of Robo Knight. Later, in a battle with the most powerful machines of evil, the Megazords of the Rangers as well as their Legendary Megazords are destroyed. After that, Troy and Orion enter the ship of Vrak and Vekar's father the Warstar Emperor Marvo, fight him, and unleash the ship's power, which destroys every other ship in the Armada. Later they both succeed in destroying Marvo and then they return to the ground. The Rangers then find that thousands of X-Borgs, the innumerable soldiers of The Armada, have been let loose on them. At this point, all the Legendary Rangers, whose powers the Rangers have been using throughout the series, appear to help them. Together, all the Rangers destroy the X-Borgs, saving the Earth.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{main|List of Power Rangers Megaforce characters}}\n\n=== Power Rangers ===\n\n* Andrew Gray as Troy Burrows, the Megaforce/Super Megaforce Red Ranger\n* [[Ciara Hanna]] as Gia Moran, the Megaforce/Super Megaforce Yellow Ranger\n* John Mark Loudermilk as Noah Carver, the Megaforce/Super Megaforce Blue Ranger\n* Christina Masterson as Emma Goodall, the Megaforce/Super Megaforce Pink Ranger\n* Azim Rizk as Jake Holling, the Megaforce Black Ranger/Super Megaforce Green Ranger\n* Chris Auer as the voice of Robo Knight\n* Cameron Jebo as Orion, the Super Megaforce Silver Ranger\n\n=== Allies ===\n* [[Geoff Dolan]] as the voices of Gosei the protege of Zordon, Gosei Morpher, and Robo Morpher\n* Estevez Gillespie as the voice of Tensou\n* Shailesh Prajapati as Ernie\n* Ian Harcourt as Mr. Burley\n*'''Legendary Rangers'''\n**[[Jason David Frank]] as [[Tommy Oliver]], the Green Ranger and the White Ranger, and subsequently Zeo Ranger V, Red, the first Red Turbo Ranger and the Black Dino Thunder Ranger.\n**[[Selwyn Ward]] as [[Theodore Jay \"T.J.\" Jarvis Johnson]], the Blue Space Ranger, and previously the second Red Turbo Ranger.\n**[[Patricia Ja Lee]] as [[Cassie Chan]], The Pink Space Ranger and previously the second Pink Turbo Ranger.\n**Danny Slavin as Leo Corbett, the Red Galaxy Ranger.\n**Reggie Rolle as [[Damon Henderson]], The Green Galaxy Ranger.\n**[[Melody Perkins]] as Karone, the second Pink Galaxy Ranger, and the former Astronema.\n**Sean Cw Johnson as Carter Grayson, the Red Lightspeed Ranger.\n**[[Alison MacInnis]] as [[Lightspeed Rescue Power Rangers#Dana Mitchell|Dana Mitchell]], the Pink Lightspeed Ranger.\n**[[Jason Faunt]] as [[Time Force Power Rangers#Wesley \"Wes\" Collins|Wesley \"Wes\" Collins]], the Red Time Force Ranger.\n**[[Jason Smith (actor)|Jason Smith]] as [[Jungle Fury Power Rangers#Casey Rhodes|Casey Rhodes]], the Red Jungle Fury Ranger.\n**[[Alex Heartman]] as Jayden Shiba, The Red Samurai Ranger.\n**Hector David Jr. as Mike, The Green Samurai Ranger.\n**[[Brittany Anne Pirtle]] as [[Samurai Power Rangers#Emily|Emily]], The Yellow Samurai Ranger.\n\n=== Villains ===\n* Jason Hood as the voice of Vrak the younger brother of Vekar, the main and primary antagonist of the series.\n* Phil Brown and Paul Harrop as the voices of Tresnag and Drill Horn\n* [[Campbell Cooley]] as the voice of Admiral Malkor\n* [[Mark Mitchinson]] as the voice of Creepox\n* Charlie McDermott as the voice of Bigs\n* [[Jay Simon]] as the voice of Bluefur\n* Sophie Henderson as the voice of Metal Alice\n* [[Andrew Laing]] as the voice of Messenger a minor villain from the Armada.\n* Stephen Butterworth as the voice of Prince Vekar the older brother of Vrak.\n* Rebecca Parr as the voice of Levira\n* Mike Drew as the voice of Emperor Marvo the father of Vrak and Vekar.\n* [[John Leigh (actor)|John Leigh]] as the voice of Damaras\n* [[Mark Wright (actor)|Mark Wright]] as the voice of Argus\n* [[Cameron Rhodes]] as the voice of Professor Cog\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n* [http://www.powerrangers.com Official Power Rangers Website]\n* {{official website|http://powerrangers.com/seasons-megaforce.php}} (''Megaforce'')\n* {{official website|http://powerrangers.com/seasons-super-megaforce.php}} (''Super Megaforce'')\n* {{official website|www.nick.com/shows/power-rangers-megaforce}} (Nickelodeon)\n* {{IMDb title|id=2236126|title=Power Rangers Megaforce}}\n\n{{Power Rangers}}\n{{Goseiger}}\n{{Gokaiger}}\n{{Former Nickelodeon original series}}\n\n[[Category:Power Rangers series|Megaforce]]\n[[Category:Power Rangers Megaforce]]\n[[Category:2013 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2014 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:2010s American high school television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American science fiction television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:Television series about size change]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in California]]\n[[Category:American children's action television series]]\n[[Category:American children's adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American children's fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by Lionsgate Television]]\n[[Category:ABS-CBN shows]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Power Rangers Megaforce\n| show_name_2              = Power Rangers Super Megaforce<br>Saban's Power Rangers Megaforce<br>Saban's Power Rangers Super Megaforce\n| image                    = Power Rangers Megaforce logo.png\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = The logo for ''Power Rangers Megaforce